<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="110">
<taxonomicName LSID="4D2F513F-2C36-5F71-B766-80CE688F6689" authority="Ducke, Anais Acad. Brasil. Ci. 7: 207. 1935. Lectotype (designated by Egler in Bol. Mus. Emilio Goeldi. Nov. Ser. Botanica. 18: 51. 1963): Brazil, Rio de Janeiro, Avelar, Faz. Pau Grande, Posse, G. M. Nunes 3 (lectotype RB!, isolectotypes MG!, R!)." authorityName="Ducke, Anais Acad. Brasil. Ci. 7: 207. 1935. Lectotype (designated by Egler in Bol. Mus. Emílio Goeldi. Nov. Ser. Botânica. 18: 51. 1963): Brazil, Rio de Janeiro, Avelar, Faz. Pau Grande, Posse, G. M. Nunes 3 (lectotype RB!, isolectotypes MG!, R!)." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Hymenaea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Hymenaea altissima" order="Fabales" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="altissima">
Hymenaea altissima Ducke, Anais Acad. Brasil. Ci. 7: 207. 1935. Lectotype (designated by Egler in Bol. Mus. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Emílio">Emilio</normalizedToken>
Goeldi. Nov. Ser. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Botânica">Botanica</normalizedToken>
. 18: 51. 1963): Brazil, Rio de Janeiro, Avelar, Faz. Pau Grande, Posse, G. M. Nunes 3 (lectotype RB!, isolectotypes MG!, R!).
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="110" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="110">
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Hymenaea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Fabales" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="courbaril">Hymenaea courbaril</taxonomicName>
var. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">altissima</emphasis>
(Ducke) Lee and Lang., J. Arnold Arbor. 55: 448. 1974.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="111" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="110">
Large trees, up to 38 m tall. Petiole 1-1.3 (-1.7) cm long; petiolule 3-4 (-5) mm long; leaflets 4-5.7 (-6.4) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-2.5 cm, oval, narrow-elliptic or elliptic, strongly falcate, due to central vein with an angle c. 35°, apex acuminate, rarely acute, base acute along the inner margin and truncate along the outer margin, distance from the inner margin to central vein 4-5 mm in the basal region. Flower buds 1.5-2.5 cm long; flower 2-2.7 cm long; hypanthium 7-12 mm long; petals 1.2-1.6 cm long. Fruit cylindrical, of uniform width, apex mostly rounded and apiculate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="111" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Hymenaea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Fabales" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="altissima">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Hymenaea altissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shows the smallest leaflets and flowers in the species group related to 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Hymenaea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Fabales" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="courbaril">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Hymenaea courbaril</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<tableCitation captionStart="Table 4" captionStartId="T4" captionText="Table 4. Morphological comparison between Hymenaea courbaril, Hymenaea altissima, and Hymenaea longifolia." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/5641E2730BBF9E181E38DFF00F620044" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" tableUuid="5641E2730BBF9E181E38DFF00F620044">Table 4</tableCitation>
). Additionally, its leaflets are strongly falcate due to the strongly curved and displaced midvein, with an abruptly acuminate apex. The base of the 
<pageBreakToken pageId="10" pageNumber="111" start="start">leaflet</pageBreakToken>
is acute along the inner margin and truncate along the outer margin (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Leaf morphology of the species recognized in the Hymenaea courbaril complex: A Hymenaea longifolia B Hymenaea courbaril C Hymenaea altissima. Scale bar = 1 cm." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/10662" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Figure 3</figureCitation>
). The fruits are mostly cylindrical, as in 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Hymenaea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Fabales" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="courbaril">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Hymenaea courbaril</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but usually shorter than those of this species (4-5 vs. 8-20 cm long) because they have only one or two seeds, while in 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Hymenaea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Fabales" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="courbaril">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Hymenaea courbaril</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
they usually have six or more seeds. This species is restricted to the coastal rain forests of eastern Brazil, from southern Bahia State to 
<normalizedToken originalValue="São">Sao</normalizedToken>
Paulo and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Paraná">Parana</normalizedToken>
states.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="10" pageNumber="111">
This species was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ducke, A" journalOrPublisher="Annaes da Academia Brasileira de Sciencias" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" pagination="203 - 212" refId="B12" refString="Ducke, A, 1935. As especies brasileiras de jatahy, jutahy ou jatoba (genero Hymenaea L., leguminosas cesalpiniaceas). Annaes da Academia Brasileira de Sciencias 7 (3): 203 - 212" title="As especies brasileiras de jatahy, jutahy ou jatoba (genero Hymenaea L., leguminosas cesalpiniaceas)." volume="7" year="1935">Ducke (1935)</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Hymenaea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Fabales" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="altissima">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Hymenaea altissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Lee, Y-T" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the Arnold Arboretum" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" pagination="441 - 452" refId="B21" refString="Lee, Y-T, Langenheim, JH, 1974. Additional new taxa and combinations in Hymenaea (Leguminosae, Caesalpinioideae). Journal of the Arnold Arboretum 55 (3): 441 - 452" title="Additional new taxa and combinations in Hymenaea (Leguminosae, Caesalpinioideae)." volume="55" year="1974">Lee and Langenheim (1974)</bibRefCitation>
treated it as a variety of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Hymenaea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Fabales" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="courbaril">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Hymenaea courbaril</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Later, these latter authors highlighted the differences between this taxon and the other varieties as having smaller and falcate leaflets and smaller flowers (
<bibRefCitation author="Lee, Y-T" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the Arnold Arboretum" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" refId="B22" refString="Lee, Y-T, Langenheim, JH, 1975. Systematics of the genus Hymenaea L. (Leguminosae, Caesalpinioideae, Detarieae). University of California Publications in Botany 69: 109." title="Systematics of the genus Hymenaea L. (Leguminosae, Caesalpinioideae, Detarieae). University of California Publications in Botany 69: 109." year="1975">Lee and Langenheim 1975</bibRefCitation>
: 86), but kept it as a variety of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Hymenaea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Fabales" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="courbaril">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Hymenaea courbaril</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a position also adopted by 
<bibRefCitation author="Pestana, LTC" journalOrPublisher="Blumea" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" refId="B30" refString="Pestana, LTC, 2010. Estudo taxonomico de Hymenea L.: complexo H. courbaril, H. martiana e H. stigonocarpa (Fabaceae: Caesalpinioidea: Detarieae). Masters thesis, Universidade Federal de Mato Grosso do Sul, Campo Grande, 45." title="Estudo taxonomico de Hymenea L.: complexo H. courbaril, H. martiana e H. stigonocarpa (Fabaceae: Caesalpinioidea: Detarieae). Masters thesis, Universidade Federal de Mato Grosso do Sul, Campo Grande, 45." year="2010">Pestana (2010)</bibRefCitation>
. Our results indicated that the leaf traits of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Hymenaea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Fabales" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="altissima">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Hymenaea altissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are clearly distinct of those of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Hymenaea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Fabales" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="courbaril">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Hymenaea courbaril</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="I. M. Souza, Funch &amp; L. P. Queiroz" authorityYear="2014" baseAuthorityName="Benth." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Hymenaea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Fabales" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="longifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Hymenaea longifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. These results, together with the distinctive flower and fruit traits and the coherent distribution and habitat data, all give support to the original view of 
<bibRefCitation author="Ducke, A" journalOrPublisher="Annaes da Academia Brasileira de Sciencias" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" pagination="203 - 212" refId="B12" refString="Ducke, A, 1935. As especies brasileiras de jatahy, jutahy ou jatoba (genero Hymenaea L., leguminosas cesalpiniaceas). Annaes da Academia Brasileira de Sciencias 7 (3): 203 - 212" title="As especies brasileiras de jatahy, jutahy ou jatoba (genero Hymenaea L., leguminosas cesalpiniaceas)." volume="7" year="1935">Ducke (1935)</bibRefCitation>
in considering it a different species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="10" pageNumber="111">
Lee and Langenheim (1975: 84) stated that the lectotype of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Hymenaea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Fabales" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="altissima">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Hymenaea altissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was designated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Egler, W" journalOrPublisher="Boletim do Museu Paraense Emilio Goeldi" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" pagination="1 - 129" refId="B13" refString="Egler, W, 1963. Adolpho Ducke-Tracos biograficos, viagens e trabalhos. Boletim do Museu Paraense Emilio Goeldi 18: 1 - 129" title="Adolpho Ducke-Tracos biograficos, viagens e trabalhos." volume="18" year="1963">Egler (1963)</bibRefCitation>
as the specimen &quot; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">A. Ducke RB 30306</emphasis>
&quot;. However, Egler (1963: 51) simply indicated that the type should be &quot;Type: RB 23.306&quot;. We could not track any specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Hymenaea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Fabales" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Hymenaea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the RB herbarium with the numbers RB 30306 or RB 23306. We encountered, however, a specimen annotated by Ducke as 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Hymenaea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Fabales" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="altissima">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Hymenaea altissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that was collected in the state of &quot;Rio de Janeiro, Avelar&quot; by G. M. Nunes in 1925 and could be linked to the protologue of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Hymenaea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Fabales" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="altissima">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Hymenaea altissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Ducke, A" journalOrPublisher="Annaes da Academia Brasileira de Sciencias" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" pagination="203 - 212" refId="B12" refString="Ducke, A, 1935. As especies brasileiras de jatahy, jutahy ou jatoba (genero Hymenaea L., leguminosas cesalpiniaceas). Annaes da Academia Brasileira de Sciencias 7 (3): 203 - 212" title="As especies brasileiras de jatahy, jutahy ou jatoba (genero Hymenaea L., leguminosas cesalpiniaceas)." volume="7" year="1935">Ducke 1935</bibRefCitation>
). This specimen is numbered RB 20306, and we are assuming that both 
<bibRefCitation author="Egler, W" journalOrPublisher="Boletim do Museu Paraense Emilio Goeldi" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" pagination="1 - 129" refId="B13" refString="Egler, W, 1963. Adolpho Ducke-Tracos biograficos, viagens e trabalhos. Boletim do Museu Paraense Emilio Goeldi 18: 1 - 129" title="Adolpho Ducke-Tracos biograficos, viagens e trabalhos." volume="18" year="1963">Egler (1963)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Lee, Y-T" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the Arnold Arboretum" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" refId="B22" refString="Lee, Y-T, Langenheim, JH, 1975. Systematics of the genus Hymenaea L. (Leguminosae, Caesalpinioideae, Detarieae). University of California Publications in Botany 69: 109." title="Systematics of the genus Hymenaea L. (Leguminosae, Caesalpinioideae, Detarieae). University of California Publications in Botany 69: 109." year="1975">Lee and Langenheim (1975)</bibRefCitation>
erroneously noted the RB number when referring to the lectotype of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Hymenaea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Fabales" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="altissima">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Hymenaea altissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
